track.name: Empire State Express
comments: Can't tell if this is one guitar or a whole damn symphony.
The instrumentation sounds like Willie Brown's "Future Blues".
Hear a lot of this in Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues...

Gerry is right, modern so-called artists mostly miss out on the experience of becoming better through bitter experience, as the estimable Son, and his contemporaries, had to do.  This track is unnerving, and sly.
Yeah Gerry, but if the delta blues men had had the chance, then they'd've taken the money and enjoyed the good things in life too- I think most of them did anyway!
Real emotion , real experience... our pampered, spoilt and too rich artists of today do not deserve to be in the same space as these Blues men!
